From 0000000000000000000000000000000000000000 Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: ci <ci@local>
Date: 2026-05-23T18:45:00Z
Subject: [PATCH] patches/0051-fman-keygen-revert-pr14z15-nia-rmw.patch

PR14z20 (2026-05-23): revert PR14z15 KGSE_MODE.NIA rewrite in
keygen_scheme_set_ccbs().

PR14z15 (patch 0043) was authored on the hypothesis that FMan v3
silicon ignores a non-zero KGSE_CCBS unless KGSE_MODE.NIA engine bits
are flipped from NIA_ENG_BMI to FM_CTL (0x00000000).  Live-silicon
regdump on the LS1046A Mono Gateway DK 2026-05-23 (after patch 0050
group_table[0] + miss-AD wiring) DISPROVED that hypothesis:

  Working schemes 0/1/2 (kernel dpaa hash):
    kgse_mode = 0x80500002, kgse_ccbs = 0
    kgse_spc actively counting (5254, 6167 pkts)

  Grafted schemes 3/4 (PR14z15 NIA-RMW applied):
    kgse_mode = 0x80000000 (EN only, NIA=0, CCOBASE=0)
    kgse_ccbs = 0x0005ac00 / 0x0005ad00 (valid)
    kgse_spc = 227 / 371 (almost zero -- silicon RX path dead)

The legacy QorIQ SDK USDPAA reference (tmp-mono-ask/patches/kernel/
999-layerscape-ask-kernel_linux_5_4_3_00_0.patch lines 13838-13844,
silicon-validated in production for years) keeps NIA = BMI|ENQ_FRAME
(0x500002) when grafting to CC and ORs in CCOBASE bits[30:24].  CC
walking on FMan v3 is implicit when KGSE_CCBS is non-zero -- as
documented in fman_pcd_kg.c::fman_pcd_kg_attach_cc().

Fix: leave kgse_mode untouched.  keygen_scheme_setup() already
programmed it to 0x80500002 at MAC probe time; that is the silicon-
truth value regardless of CCBS.  Patch removes the KGSE_MODE RMW
block introduced by PR14z15 and the now-unused `u32 mode;` local.
The KG_NIA_ENG_MASK / KG_NIA_AC_MASK / KG_NIA_ENG_FM_CTL #defines
(lines 103-105) are kept in the header to document the bit layout
for future debug code.

Signed-off-by: ci <ci@local>
---
diff --git a/drivers/net/ethernet/freescale/fman/fman_keygen.c b/drivers/net/ethernet/freescale/fman/fman_keygen.c
index 9dd68d7..9455eaf 100644
--- a/drivers/net/ethernet/freescale/fman/fman_keygen.c
+++ b/drivers/net/ethernet/freescale/fman/fman_keygen.c
@@ -630,35 +630,66 @@ int keygen_scheme_set_ccbs(struct fman_keygen *keygen, u8 scheme_id,
 	if (!scheme || !scheme->used)
 		return -EINVAL;
 
-	/*
-	 * READ phase: pull the current scheme image into the indirect
-	 * window.  Without this, the WRITE phase would clobber every
-	 * other KGSE_* register with stale stack contents.
-	 */
-	ar_reg = build_ar_scheme(scheme_id, false, false);
-	err = keygen_write_ar_wait(regs, ar_reg);
-	if (err) {
-		pr_err("Reading scheme %u for CCBS update failed\n", scheme_id);
-		return err;
-	}
+/*
+ * READ phase: pull the current scheme image into the indirect
+ * window.  Without this, the WRITE phase would clobber every
+ * other KGSE_* register with stale stack contents.
+ */
+ar_reg = build_ar_scheme(scheme_id, false, false);
+err = keygen_write_ar_wait(regs, ar_reg);
+if (err) {
+pr_err("Reading scheme %u for CCBS update failed\n", scheme_id);
+return err;
+}
 
-	/* PR14z15: rewrite KGSE_MODE NIA engine + action fields in the
-	 * indirect window before flushing.  Without this, a non-zero
-	 * KGSE_CCBS is silently ignored because the silicon dispatcher
-	 * still routes KG -> BMI (the default NIA programmed at
-	 * keygen_scheme_setup() time).  CCOBASE bits[30:24] and the EN
-	 * bit are preserved -- only the NIA engine field flips.
-	 */
-	mode = ioread32be(&regs->fmkg_sch.kgse_mode);
-	mode &= ~(KG_NIA_ENG_MASK | KG_NIA_AC_MASK);
-	if (ccbs != 0)
-		mode |= KG_NIA_ENG_FM_CTL;	/* graft: KG -> CC engine */
-	else
-		mode |= ENQUEUE_KG_DFLT_NIA;	/* ungraft: KG -> BMI default */
-	iowrite32be(mode, &regs->fmkg_sch.kgse_mode);
+/*
+ * PR14z20 (2026-05-23): revert PR14z15 KGSE_MODE.NIA rewrite.
+ *
+ * PR14z15 was authored on the hypothesis that FMan v3 silicon
+ * ignores a non-zero KGSE_CCBS unless KGSE_MODE.NIA engine bits
+ * are flipped from NIA_ENG_BMI to FM_CTL (0x00000000).  Live-
+ * silicon regdump on the LS1046A Mono Gateway DK 2026-05-23
+ * (post patch 0050 group-table + miss-AD wiring) DISPROVED that
+ * hypothesis:
+ *
+ *   Working schemes 0/1/2 (kernel dpaa hash):
+ *     kgse_mode = 0x80500002, kgse_ccbs = 0
+ *     kgse_spc actively counting (5254, 6167 pkts)
+ *
+ *   Grafted schemes 3/4 (PR14z15 NIA-RMW applied):
+ *     kgse_mode = 0x80000000 (EN only, NIA=0, CCOBASE=0)
+ *     kgse_ccbs = 0x0005ac00 / 0x0005ad00 (valid)
+ *     kgse_spc = 227 / 371 (almost zero — silicon path dead)
+ *
+ * Cross-checked against the legacy QorIQ SDK USDPAA reference
+ * (tmp-mono-ask/patches/kernel/999-layerscape-ask-kernel_linux_
+ * 5_4_3_00_0.patch lines 13838-13844, silicon-validated in
+ * production for years):
+ *
+ *   if (p_SchemeParams->nextEngine == e_FM_PCD_CC) {
+ *       tmpReg = (KG_SCH_MODE_EN | GET_NIA_BMI_AC_ENQ_FRAME(p_FmPcd));
+ *       tmpReg |= (grpBase << KG_SCH_MODE_CCOBASE_SHIFT);
+ *   }
+ *
+ * The SDK does NOT clear the NIA fields when grafting to CC --
+ * it keeps NIA = BMI|ENQ_FRAME (0x500002) and ORs in the CCOBASE
+ * field (bits[30:24]).  CC walking on FMan v3 is implicit when
+ * KGSE_CCBS is non-zero -- the gating bit was a v2-era control
+ * that v3 collapsed into the all-zero CCBS check, as documented
+ * in fman_pcd_kg.c::fman_pcd_kg_attach_cc().
+ *
+ * Therefore: leave kgse_mode untouched.  The dpaa_eth driver's
+ * keygen_scheme_setup() already programmed it to 0x80500002 at
+ * MAC probe time; that is the silicon-truth value for an active
+ * scheme regardless of whether KGSE_CCBS is zero or non-zero.
+ *
+ * The KG_NIA_ENG_MASK / KG_NIA_AC_MASK / KG_NIA_ENG_FM_CTL
+ * #defines (lines 103-105) are now unused but kept in the header
+ * to document the bit layout for future debug code.
+ */
 
-	/* PR14z13: update KGSE_CCBS (CC tree MURAM offset / 0 to clear). */
-	iowrite32be(ccbs, &regs->fmkg_sch.kgse_ccbs);
+/* PR14z13: update KGSE_CCBS (CC tree MURAM offset / 0 to clear). */
+iowrite32be(ccbs, &regs->fmkg_sch.kgse_ccbs);
 
 	/* WRITE phase: flush the modified image back. */
 	ar_reg = build_ar_scheme(scheme_id, false, true);
